<item>
            <title>[LU-3967] Add history support for lprocfs_stats</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3967</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In order to check the impact of TBF and other NRS policies, we adds a counter which collocts the counts of handled requests during differnt time periods (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3495&quot; title=&quot;Count the request rates of ptlrpc services&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3495&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3495&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). After more consideration, we think that there might be a wider range of use to keep the track of eneral&lt;br/&gt;
lproc_stats than RPC count only. The former implementation of RPC count history can be&lt;br/&gt;
easily replaced by a general implementation, so we decided to port the old codes to lprocfs and mananged to add a history support for lprocfs_stats. It might be helpful for users to collect information about the system in some cases including NRS policy tuning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch will be post soon.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
